==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|gussie up}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|*}}

# {{lb|en|informal|intransitive}} To [[don]] fancy clothing; to [[dress up]] particularly in flattering or specially altered garments.
#: {{ux|en|You bet she'll '''gussy up''' for the party.}}
#: {{syn|en|doll up}}
# {{lb|en|informal|transitive}} To make [[fancy]] or [[attractive]], as by [[artificial]] or [[contrived]] means.
#: {{ux|en|You can have plain green beans, or '''gussie''' them '''up''' with a bit of cheese and onion.}}
#: {{syn|en|spruce up}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Jennifer Szalai|title=In ‘Rationality,’ Steven Pinker Sticks Up (Again) for Reason’s Role in Human Progress|work=The New York Times|date=2021-09-29|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/09/29/books/review-rationality-steven-pinker.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=The trouble arrives when he tries to '''gussy up''' his psychologist’s hat with his more elaborate public intellectual’s attire.}}

